# Our Setup, Import Libaries, Create our Imshow Function and Download our Images
import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

# Define our imshow function 
def imshow(title = "Image", image = None, size = 10):
    w, h = image.shape[0], image.shape[1]
    aspect_ratio = w/h
    plt.figure(figsize=(size * aspect_ratio,size))
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

# M matrixni rasmga qo'shamiz. 
# Brightness ni oshirish uchun
added = cv2.add(image, M)
imshow("Increasing Brightness", added) #shunning uchun Opencv dan add funksoyadidan foydalanish kerak.

# Agar shunchaki numpy orqali sonlarni qoshsak qanday bo'ladi. 
#Rasm o'z xususiyatini buzib tashlaydi 
added2 = image + M 
imshow("Oddiy numpy bn intensitylarni qo'shish orqali", added2)

Ikkinchi rasm buzilishining sababi, rasmdagi ayrim pixellar intensitysi 200 bolishi mumkun va bunga 100 qo'shilgan, yangi rasmda o'sha pixel value 300 bo'lib keradi bunday rang value esa yo'q shu sababli np 300-255=45 300 yoki umuman 255 dan katta bo'lib ketgan qismlarni 0 ga tushirib hisoblab qoyadi. Misol: 300 bolgan pixellarni yangi rasmda 45 dagi qiymat bilan almashib ko'rinadi

# If you're wondering why only two dimensions, well this is a grayscale image, 

# Making a square
square = np.zeros((300, 300), np.uint8)
cv2.rectangle(square, (50, 50), (250, 250), 255, -2) 
imshow("square", square)

# Making a ellipse
ellipse = np.zeros((300, 300), np.uint8)
#img to draw, (centerx, centery), ()
cv2.ellipse(ellipse, (150, 150), (150, 150), 30, 0, 180, 255, -1)
imshow("ellipse", ellipse)

AND, OR, XOR and NOT¶

LINK: https://pyimagesearch.com/2021/01/19/opencv-bitwise-and-or-xor-and-not/ AND: A bitwise AND is true if and only if both pixels are greater than zero. OR: A bitwise OR is true if either of the two pixels is greater than zero. XOR: A bitwise XOR is true if and only if one of the two pixels is greater than zero, but not both. NOT: A bitwise NOT inverts the on and off pixels in an image.
In [28]:
# Faqatgina ikkalasi qo'shilgan joyni oladi. Kesishgan joyni 
And = cv2.bitwise_and(square, ellipse)
imshow("AND", And)

# OR va ikkalasi ham mavjud qismni oladi
bitwiseOr = cv2.bitwise_or(square, ellipse)
imshow("bitwiseOr", bitwiseOr)

# Ikkalasining o'zi qaerda mavjudligini ko'rsatadi
bitwiseXor = cv2.bitwise_xor(square, ellipse)
imshow("bitwiseXor", bitwiseXor)

# Square dagi ranglarni invert qiladi. Yani va qorani rangdagi placelarni orinlarini almashtiradi
bitwiseNot_sq = cv2.bitwise_not(square)
imshow("bitwiseNot_sq", bitwiseNot_sq)

# Notice the last operation inverts the image totally
